import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['budgetYear'], bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.xlabel('Budget Year')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of budgetYear?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.75)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecastYear'])]
    data['forecastYear'] = data['forecastYear'].dt.year

    plt.plot(data['forecastYear'], data['value'], label='Value')
    plt.xlabel('Forecast Year')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    plt.title('Distribution of Forecast Year', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['value'])
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of value?')
    ax.set_ylabel('Value')
    ax.axhline(data['value'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['value'].median():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
